cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.AI 

The paper deals with the determinization of Buchi automata, which is a problem in formal languages and automata theory. The use of profiles and trees in the construction is related to logic and order theory, which suggests the cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) category. The paper also mentions applications in synthesis, probabilistic verification, and multi-agent systems, which are related to formal methods and artificial intelligence, suggesting the cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) categories. Finally, the paper introduces a new declarative construction for determinization, which is related to programming languages and semantics, suggesting the cs.PL (Programming Languages) category.
